# Observability Readiness

Application: `{{ app.name }}`
Namespace: `{{ app.namespace }}`
Metrics endpoint: `{{ observability.metrics.path }}`
ServiceMonitor namespace: `{{ service_monitor_namespace }}`
Grafana dashboard title: `{{ dashboard_title }}`

This directory contains local observability readiness files generated from `app.yaml`.
`k8s-forge` does not install Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, kube-prometheus-stack, Promtail, or OpenTelemetry Collector. It does not create secrets, does not call Grafana APIs, does not run `kubectl apply`, and does not run `helm install`.

## What Observability Means Here

Observability helps operators understand what the application and cluster are doing.

- Metrics are numeric time series scraped by systems such as Prometheus.
- Logs are event records emitted by applications and infrastructure.
- Traces follow a request across services.

v0.11.0 focuses on metrics readiness with Prometheus Operator `ServiceMonitor` and a local Grafana dashboard JSON example. Loki logs and tracing are future work.

## Generated Files

- `prometheus/servicemonitor.yaml`: Prometheus Operator `ServiceMonitor` example.
{% if observability.grafana.enabled and observability.grafana.dashboard.enabled -%}
- `grafana/dashboard.json`: local Grafana dashboard JSON model to import manually.
{% endif %}

## Prerequisites

The `ServiceMonitor` requires Prometheus Operator CRDs from `monitoring.coreos.com`. If those CRDs are missing, Kubernetes will reject the object. That is normal for readiness-only generation.

The application must expose a real metrics endpoint at `{{ observability.metrics.path }}` before Prometheus can scrape useful metrics.

## Review Commands

```bash
cat prometheus/servicemonitor.yaml
{% if observability.grafana.enabled and observability.grafana.dashboard.enabled -%}
cat grafana/dashboard.json
{% endif -%}
k8s-forge doctor
```

## Scope v0.11.0

- Prometheus Operator `ServiceMonitor` readiness only;
- local Grafana dashboard JSON only;
- no Prometheus or Grafana installation;
- no Loki, Promtail, or OpenTelemetry Collector;
- no Grafana datasource or API call;
- no credentials or secrets;
- no automatic apply or Helm install;
- alerts are accepted in configuration but not rendered yet.
